1
00:00:10,690 --> 00:00:11,690
Fuu.

2
00:00:13,910 --> 00:00:15,110
I'm so glad you're okay.

3
00:00:20,340 --> 00:00:21,840
The parallel world...

4
00:00:31,710 --> 00:00:33,320
I finally found you, Fuu.

5
00:00:50,250 --> 00:00:51,250
The paper cup phone.

6
00:00:53,210 --> 00:00:54,510
Knock, knock, knock.

7
00:00:57,900 --> 00:00:59,690
If he doesn't know who I am,

8
00:01:01,410 --> 00:01:03,210
then I'll just start over
from the beginning.

9
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,760
You finally called yourself "Fuu."

10
00:01:14,330 --> 00:01:15,330
Fuu...

11
00:01:18,520 --> 00:01:19,520
I love you.

12
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:22,190
But right now, we're supposed to be lovers,

13
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:25,040
aren't we?

14
00:01:25,080 --> 00:01:26,910
But I'll be by your side forever.

15
00:01:31,250 --> 00:01:32,350
Who are you?

16
00:01:34,880 --> 00:01:36,800
The one Sara-senpai truly loves...

17
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:39,920
The one he wants to
protect for the rest of his life...

18
00:01:40,540 --> 00:01:41,740
It isn't this Fuu, is it?

19
00:01:42,430 --> 00:01:44,220
I love Sara-senpai.

20
00:01:45,780 --> 00:01:47,310
I truly, deeply love him.

21
00:02:02,070 --> 00:02:03,070
Here we go again...

22
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,500
(I hope you feel better soon.)

23
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:01,320
No.

24
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:06,600
A person?

25
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:08,840
A cat?

26
00:03:10,530 --> 00:03:11,530
Just come out already.

27
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:15,940
I'm gonna throw this away.

28
00:03:21,350 --> 00:03:22,860
If you want something, come out.

29
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:27,810
You're such an eyesore.

30
00:03:27,930 --> 00:03:28,930
Brat.

31
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:37,280
Sara-senpai took it!

32
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,500
Yes! I'm so lucky!

33
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:49,800
"The Boy Next World My Destiny"
(Special Episode 1)

34
00:04:53,860 --> 00:04:55,260
Once you notice something,

35
00:04:56,340 --> 00:04:57,780
you can't stop thinking about it.

36
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:10,570
Do you have a screw loose or something?

37
00:05:12,470 --> 00:05:14,500
He noticed me!

38
00:05:14,710 --> 00:05:16,060
And I actually talked to him!

39
00:05:16,470 --> 00:05:17,470
Fuu...

40
00:05:17,510 --> 00:05:20,140
Watching from afar
doesn't count as progress.

41
00:05:20,340 --> 00:05:23,500
You can't be friends with
someone you're just stalking.

42
00:05:23,620 --> 00:05:24,686
Just because you pass
each other in the hall

43
00:05:24,710 --> 00:05:26,020
doesn't mean it's mutual.

44
00:05:26,620 --> 00:05:28,070
I'm telling you, we really talked!

45
00:05:30,290 --> 00:05:31,290
You've got it bad.

46
00:05:31,690 --> 00:05:34,530
- Should I take you to a doctor?
- I don't think the nurse can fix this.

47
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:40,830
Seriously, Fuu.

48
00:05:41,270 --> 00:05:43,980
How many years have you
crushed on Sara-senpai?

49
00:05:44,980 --> 00:05:48,570
We've watched you do
this since high school.

50
00:05:49,220 --> 00:05:52,060
Have you ever even looked him in the eye?

51
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:54,320
When did you even talk to him?

52
00:05:55,190 --> 00:05:56,190
In your dreams?

53
00:05:57,020 --> 00:05:58,029
I'm not lying!

54
00:05:58,030 --> 00:05:59,070
Sure, sure.

55
00:05:59,550 --> 00:06:00,042
Oh...

56
00:06:00,401 --> 00:06:01,401
I totally believe you.

57
00:06:01,980 --> 00:06:03,380
You don't believe me at all!

58
00:06:03,770 --> 00:06:04,870
Well, can you blame us?

59
00:06:05,150 --> 00:06:06,900
The only time Fuu ever showed any guts

60
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:08,510
was during *that* incident.

61
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:12,450
I'll never forget it.

62
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:14,590
The legendary "Smile Thief."

63
00:06:15,070 --> 00:06:16,439
Hey, it wasn't exactly stealing.

64
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:17,680
You totally stole it.

65
00:06:17,700 --> 00:06:19,660
That was university property!

66
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:24,000
(You should join the student council too!)

67
00:06:35,050 --> 00:06:36,050
That was hilarious.

68
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:37,780
You ran away so fast.

69
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:39,120
I wasn't trying to steal it!

70
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,570
Then give it back.

71
00:06:40,580 --> 00:06:41,749
He's never giving it back.

72
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:43,310
It's probably a family heirloom by now.

73
00:06:43,810 --> 00:06:44,810
Anyway,

74
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:47,510
why do you even like Sara-senpai?

75
00:06:47,910 --> 00:06:49,209
He's handsome, sure,

76
00:06:49,210 --> 00:06:50,540
but he's got such a sharp tongue.

77
00:06:50,630 --> 00:06:52,390
Everyone says he'd be perfect

78
00:06:52,415 --> 00:06:53,775
if he just never opened his mouth.

79
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:01,470
Back in high school,

80
00:07:01,471 --> 00:07:03,559
I accidentally left my paper
cup phone in his classroom.

81
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,240
When I went back to get it,

82
00:07:04,241 --> 00:07:06,040
I overheard him on the phone with his dad.

83
00:07:06,490 --> 00:07:07,599
He sounded harsh,

84
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:09,179
but he was so polite to his father

85
00:07:09,180 --> 00:07:10,700
and he really cared about his brother.

86
00:07:11,310 --> 00:07:14,350
His parents are divorced, and
his brother lives with his dad.

87
00:07:14,910 --> 00:07:16,490
Back then, he told his father...

88
00:07:16,830 --> 00:07:17,830
He said...

89
00:07:20,450 --> 00:07:22,970
"Dad, I'll take care of myself."

90
00:07:23,090 --> 00:07:25,350
"I'll take care of you and
Soshi too, just wait for me."

91
00:07:26,330 --> 00:07:27,360
It was so cool.

92
00:07:27,630 --> 00:07:28,120
And also,

93
00:07:28,121 --> 00:07:30,320
when his friend Taiga-senpai broke his leg,

94
00:07:30,490 --> 00:07:32,730
he complained the whole
time but still took care of him.

95
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,320
How can someone be so cute?

96
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,680
Plus, his voice is amazing.

97
00:07:36,970 --> 00:07:38,800
He's just perfect.

98
00:07:41,550 --> 00:07:43,330
Oh, I have to go!

99
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:45,070
His class should be ending soon.

100
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:46,870
I need to check if he's feeling better.

101
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:48,440
Go on then.

102
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:49,230
See ya.

103
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:50,580
Bye!

104
00:07:53,180 --> 00:07:54,800
Fuu is usually so shy.

105
00:07:55,230 --> 00:07:58,120
How does he talk so much
when it's about Sara-senpai?

106
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:02,140
At this rate, he'll end up in
the hospital from lovesickness.

107
00:08:02,420 --> 00:08:04,110
We knew he liked him, but...

108
00:08:04,990 --> 00:08:06,260
did he really talk to him?

109
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:07,750
Who knows.

110
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:12,080
Man, I'm starving.

111
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,270
You really saved a seat?

112
00:08:14,630 --> 00:08:16,830
It's a pain to find one
once it gets crowded.

113
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:18,886
Besides, I'm always the
one who has to find them.

114
00:08:18,910 --> 00:08:19,910
Well, obviously.

115
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:21,720
You've got a sharp eye for these things.

116
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,620
You've got some nerve.

117
00:08:22,621 --> 00:08:24,589
You notice everything,

118
00:08:24,590 --> 00:08:26,170
yet you dump all the hard work on me.

119
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:29,720
Here.

120
00:08:29,910 --> 00:08:30,980
I'll go get the food.

121
00:08:31,690 --> 00:08:33,550
You just stay here and talk to yourself.

122
00:08:34,070 --> 00:08:36,430
Don't treat me like a chore!

123
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:55,200
(Please have this.)

124
00:09:03,370 --> 00:09:04,370
Oh?

125
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,080
Another fan?

126
00:09:07,170 --> 00:09:08,790
There's even a note.

127
00:09:11,250 --> 00:09:13,380
"Please habe this," huh?

128
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:16,430
You never drink the stuff people give you.

129
00:09:19,780 --> 00:09:20,780
Wait.

130
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,440
You're actually drinking it?

131
00:09:23,180 --> 00:09:24,720
You usually won't even touch them.

132
00:09:25,870 --> 00:09:30,510
I just felt like it today.

133
00:09:30,792 --> 00:09:32,412
That's weird.

134
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:35,580
Maybe I should just throw it away.

135
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:37,280
No.

136
00:09:37,670 --> 00:09:39,030
I'll keep it.

137
00:09:39,850 --> 00:09:40,850
You want some?

138
00:09:41,460 --> 00:09:42,500
Oh, wait...

139
00:09:42,710 --> 00:09:44,700
It's just a drink. Why
are you being so weird?

140
00:09:44,850 --> 00:09:46,480
- Give it here, I'll drink it.
- No way.

141
00:09:47,410 --> 00:09:48,410
I'm drinking it.

142
00:09:48,550 --> 00:09:49,550
This is mine.

143
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:51,650
- Just hand it over!
- Hey, give it back!

144
00:09:52,390 --> 00:09:53,970
Give it back, I said!

145
00:09:55,270 --> 00:09:56,940
Why don't you just talk to Sara-senpai?

146
00:09:58,670 --> 00:10:00,070
I don't have the guts.

147
00:10:00,890 --> 00:10:02,490
Are you just gonna keep this up forever?

148
00:10:04,180 --> 00:10:05,180
What do you mean?

149
00:10:06,170 --> 00:10:07,660
"What do I mean?"

150
00:10:13,742 --> 00:10:17,012
You asked me to join the student
council to help you get close to him.

151
00:10:17,280 --> 00:10:19,360
Even Taiga-senpai said he'd help you out.

152
00:10:19,380 --> 00:10:20,930
But then you turned it down.

153
00:10:21,470 --> 00:10:23,830
You said watching him from afar was enough.

154
00:10:25,430 --> 00:10:27,069
It is. I'm happy with that.

155
00:10:27,070 --> 00:10:28,430
Do you really think that's enough?

156
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,720
I still remember.

157
00:10:32,090 --> 00:10:33,720
When he had that cold,

158
00:10:33,810 --> 00:10:36,030
you were so worried you
looked like you'd collapse.

159
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:39,030
If you want to know him better,

160
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:41,430
you have to step into his world.

161
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:44,630
I told you, I don't have the guts.

162
00:10:45,490 --> 00:10:47,460
I'm fine just watching from a distance.

163
00:10:53,160 --> 00:10:54,160
It's Taiga-senpai.

164
00:11:04,150 --> 00:11:05,830
Fuu, I've got good news!

165
00:11:06,420 --> 00:11:07,840
Huh? Good news?

166
00:11:10,430 --> 00:11:12,080
Sara was asking about you.

167
00:11:13,270 --> 00:11:14,270
What?

168
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:17,050
Your hard work is finally paying off!

169
00:11:17,620 --> 00:11:18,820
No, no, what do I do?

170
00:11:19,020 --> 00:11:20,020
Shouldn't you be happy?

171
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:22,420
I won't be able to stalk him anymore!

172
00:11:22,670 --> 00:11:24,010
He's gonna think I'm a creep.

173
00:11:25,280 --> 00:11:26,299
It's not like I stole his
used forks or anything...

174
00:11:26,300 --> 00:11:28,440
Whoa, calm down.

175
00:11:30,140 --> 00:11:31,140
What am I gonna do?

176
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:33,080
What do I do?

177
00:11:33,230 --> 00:11:34,790
What do I do?!

178
00:11:38,860 --> 00:11:40,620
Didn't you say you had
something to tell me?

179
00:11:42,050 --> 00:11:43,050
Oh, right. Fuu.

180
00:11:43,860 --> 00:11:45,329
The student council's annual

181
00:11:45,330 --> 00:11:46,650
camping trip is coming up, right?

182
00:11:47,050 --> 00:11:48,580
Oh... yeah.

183
00:11:48,590 --> 00:11:49,590
It's this weekend.

184
00:11:51,630 --> 00:11:52,830
Sara's going to be there.

185
00:11:53,330 --> 00:11:54,530
You're coming too, right, Fuu?

186
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:58,040
This is the perfect chance.

187
00:12:06,550 --> 00:12:09,540
What's with that face?
We're going camping! It'll be fun.

188
00:12:09,730 --> 00:12:10,840
I'll go.

189
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:13,536
But in exchange, for the three
times the professor calls roll...

190
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:15,669
- You have to cover for me.
- Fine, fine. Now smile!

191
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:16,806
Just like you did on that poster.

192
00:12:16,830 --> 00:12:18,240
You still owe me for that one.

193
00:12:20,610 --> 00:12:21,490
Morning.

194
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:22,670
Oh, morning.

195
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:26,150
Are you holding in a sneeze?

196
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:27,680
No.

197
00:12:27,850 --> 00:12:29,230
- Morning.
- Hey there.

198
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:31,240
Hey, you guys, move to the back.

199
00:12:31,450 --> 00:12:33,080
- Sit further in.
- I'm getting on first.

200
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:34,220
Wait.

201
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:35,780
Fuu, you take that seat in the front.

202
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:37,280
Go ahead.

203
00:12:43,170 --> 00:12:44,370
We're gonna chat for a bit.

204
00:12:45,620 --> 00:12:46,740
Everyone's already on board.

205
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:48,680
Um... well...

206
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:49,900
Uh...

207
00:12:50,450 --> 00:12:51,650
Aren't you sitting with me?

208
00:12:51,940 --> 00:12:53,380
I'm sitting with Taiga-senpai.

209
00:12:55,070 --> 00:12:56,270
Then who's sitting next to me?

210
00:12:56,340 --> 00:12:57,380
He'll be here in a second.

211
00:12:58,350 --> 00:12:59,350
Just wait.

212
00:13:02,550 --> 00:13:04,070
Getting on last makes you stand out.

213
00:13:04,430 --> 00:13:05,530
You're so childish.

214
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:06,820
Let go of me already.

215
00:13:06,910 --> 00:13:08,110
I'm getting on the bus.

216
00:13:10,450 --> 00:13:11,770
Alright, go ahead.

217
00:13:26,970 --> 00:13:28,050
This is the only seat left?

218
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:54,200
Are you an idiot?

219
00:13:56,130 --> 00:13:57,130
It's okay.

220
00:13:57,570 --> 00:13:58,670
Please don't mind me.

221
00:14:00,890 --> 00:14:01,890
I *do* mind.

222
00:14:11,790 --> 00:14:13,070
Why did you run away last time?

223
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:15,560
I didn't run away.

224
00:14:16,020 --> 00:14:18,250
I thought there was a ghost at my door.

225
00:14:18,930 --> 00:14:20,309
If you're worried about how I'm feeling,

226
00:14:20,310 --> 00:14:21,520
just ask me directly.

227
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:25,600
Isn't it hard to breathe like that?

228
00:14:27,250 --> 00:14:28,250
I'm fine.

229
00:14:28,251 --> 00:14:29,350
I'm a turtle.

230
00:14:32,190 --> 00:14:33,190
Come out of there.

231
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:35,020
Stick your head out.

232
00:14:37,540 --> 00:14:38,740
I'm going to sleep.

233
00:14:42,390 --> 00:14:43,770
Alright, let's head out!

234
00:14:44,220 --> 00:14:45,660
Yeah!

235
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:48,550
I'm so excited!

236
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,020
I really can't sleep.

237
00:14:52,380 --> 00:14:54,410
I got less than two hours. I'm exhausted.

238
00:14:56,280 --> 00:14:57,810
Maybe I should try to sleep.

239
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:01,550
- Yutori, you okay?
- Yeah, I'll manage.

240
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:02,680
Right, right, right.

241
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,600
- Oh, does this go here?
- Over here?

242
00:15:05,980 --> 00:15:06,980
This way.

243
00:15:07,990 --> 00:15:08,990
Come on, come on!

244
00:15:09,220 --> 00:15:10,220
One, two, lift!

245
00:15:11,060 --> 00:15:12,060
Nice.

246
00:15:12,180 --> 00:15:13,180
Alright, everyone!

247
00:15:13,190 --> 00:15:16,320
Welcome to the Student Council's
"Heart-Pounding Camping" trip!

248
00:15:17,030 --> 00:15:18,030
Are you guys excited?

249
00:15:19,850 --> 00:15:20,850
Let's hear some applause!

250
00:15:21,590 --> 00:15:22,940
Come on, clap it up!

251
00:15:25,970 --> 00:15:27,210
Okay, okay, that's enough.

252
00:15:28,060 --> 00:15:30,150
So, I have some good news for you all.

253
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:32,470
When you say "good news," it's usually bad.

254
00:15:32,690 --> 00:15:34,320
Hey, don't interrupt. Just listen.

255
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:36,120
And that is...

256
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:37,520
Tonight,

257
00:15:38,770 --> 00:15:39,986
we don't have any place to stay!

258
00:15:40,010 --> 00:15:41,010
Let's hear it!

259
00:15:41,011 --> 00:15:43,270
- What?
- Wait, what?!

260
00:15:43,450 --> 00:15:45,550
Alright, alright, everyone calm down.

261
00:15:45,890 --> 00:15:47,089
This is camping, after all.

262
00:15:47,090 --> 00:15:48,249
What's a trip without a little adventure?

263
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:49,370
Become one with the earth...

264
00:15:49,410 --> 00:15:51,310
and breathe in the
fresh scent of the grass.

265
00:15:51,690 --> 00:15:52,719
Basically, we're sleeping in tents tonight.

266
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:53,390
Taiga-senpai!

267
00:15:53,391 --> 00:15:55,099
This isn't what you told us.

268
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:56,600
It's a surprise!

269
00:15:56,650 --> 00:15:57,520
But don't worry.

270
00:15:57,521 --> 00:16:00,081
- The bedding is ready, and the tents are fully equipped.
- Yeah.

271
00:16:01,230 --> 00:16:02,530
How are we splitting into tents?

272
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:03,936
We're going to decide with a game.

273
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:05,029
It's a game for pairs.

274
00:16:05,030 --> 00:16:06,839
The first team to collect three numbers

275
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,659
gets to sleep in the biggest tent.

276
00:16:08,660 --> 00:16:10,630
It's super spacious and comfortable.

277
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:11,420
By the way,

278
00:16:11,421 --> 00:16:13,381
the last-place team only
gets tiny sleeping bags.

279
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:14,676
Taiga-senpai, I have a question.

280
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:16,450
How are the pairs being chosen?

281
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:18,230
They've actually already been decided.

282
00:16:18,410 --> 00:16:19,410
What do you mean?

283
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:21,440
Whoever you were sitting
next to is your partner.

284
00:16:22,470 --> 00:16:24,150
Awesome!

285
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:27,840
Huh?

286
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,520
Taiga, does that mean I'm alone?

287
00:16:30,260 --> 00:16:31,800
Stop making such a fuss.

288
00:16:33,710 --> 00:16:35,600
You two were sitting together anyway.

289
00:16:36,260 --> 00:16:37,270
Must be nice.

290
00:16:38,340 --> 00:16:39,980
Alright, let's get into our groups!

291
00:16:43,340 --> 00:16:45,060
Looking forward to it.

292
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:49,470
Taiga-senpai...

293
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:51,230
Okay, it's settled!

294
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:52,750
Now for the first hint.

295
00:16:52,930 --> 00:16:54,619
First place gets the big tent.

296
00:16:54,620 --> 00:16:55,988
Last ones to the finish
line get the sleeping bags.

297
00:16:56,012 --> 00:16:56,460
Got it.

298
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:57,840
Don't forget!

299
00:16:58,460 --> 00:16:59,580
- Wait, what?
- Don't forget!

300
00:16:59,670 --> 00:17:01,420
Alright, good luck with the riddles!

301
00:17:07,670 --> 00:17:09,140
They look like they're having fun.

302
00:17:09,930 --> 00:17:11,420
I really want to try it.

303
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:22,720
Taiga-senpai,

304
00:17:23,430 --> 00:17:24,430
please change the rules.

305
00:17:24,609 --> 00:17:25,200
I'm begging you.

306
00:17:25,201 --> 00:17:26,260
No.

307
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:28,490
Taiga-senpai...

308
00:17:28,590 --> 00:17:31,260
Get going. If you lose,
you're in a sleeping bag.

309
00:17:32,340 --> 00:17:33,820
Do you want Sara to be uncomfortable?

310
00:17:34,490 --> 00:17:35,490
We can't have that, can we?
Right?

311
00:17:36,331 --> 00:17:38,040
Well... good luck with the game.

312
00:17:40,230 --> 00:17:41,590
This is a great opportunity.

313
00:17:43,210 --> 00:17:44,210
What do you mean?

314
00:17:44,211 --> 00:17:46,320
You need to show him how reliable you are!

315
00:17:46,730 --> 00:17:48,029
Maybe you can go from
being just acquaintances

316
00:17:48,030 --> 00:17:50,060
to being close juniors.

317
00:17:50,090 --> 00:17:51,090
Just like us.

318
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:52,720
Really?

319
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:53,820
Do you think he'll see it that way?

320
00:17:53,821 --> 00:17:54,860
Trust me.

321
00:17:59,170 --> 00:18:00,370
So this is where you were.

322
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:02,620
You're slow as a turtle.

323
00:18:03,140 --> 00:18:06,430
Let's go! Let's finish this jerk's game.

324
00:18:06,740 --> 00:18:08,020
Who are you calling a jerk?

325
00:18:10,470 --> 00:18:11,470
I...

326
00:18:11,510 --> 00:18:12,510
didn't say anything.

327
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:15,000
You're gonna get it when this is over.

328
00:18:16,460 --> 00:18:17,460
Let's go.

329
00:18:27,730 --> 00:18:28,850
I have to play the game too?

330
00:18:33,230 --> 00:18:34,670
Why don't you just read my mind?

331
00:18:36,220 --> 00:18:37,860
But I want to hear it from your own lips.

332
00:18:38,590 --> 00:18:40,089
Even if I can read your mind,

333
00:18:40,090 --> 00:18:41,556
I still want to hear you say it yourself.

334
00:18:41,580 --> 00:18:42,940
Of course you're sleeping with me.

335
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:44,930
But won't people say that's unfair?

336
00:18:45,060 --> 00:18:46,890
You're the student
council president's lover.

337
00:18:47,180 --> 00:18:48,480
Just enjoy the perks.

338
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:50,320
We're staying in a cabin.

339
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:52,960
No tents, no waking up with a sore back.

340
00:18:53,150 --> 00:18:54,150
Right?

341
00:19:00,690 --> 00:19:01,690
Let's go.

342
00:19:06,380 --> 00:19:08,140
Mountain spirits under the tree.

343
00:19:09,110 --> 00:19:11,370
Head toward the 3 o'clock position.

344
00:19:14,710 --> 00:19:16,220
What kind of stupid hint is that?

345
00:19:17,380 --> 00:19:20,220
Taiga, just you wait.

346
00:19:23,860 --> 00:19:24,860
Ah!

347
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:34,200
You're such a burden.

348
00:19:36,590 --> 00:19:37,620
I'm sorry.

349
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:39,370
Walk faster.

350
00:19:44,020 --> 00:19:45,020
Pull it together, Fuu.

351
00:19:45,460 --> 00:19:47,230
Don't be a burden. You can do this.

352
00:19:54,350 --> 00:19:56,030
Sara-senpai, I found it!

353
00:20:06,150 --> 00:20:09,650
"Idiot. At this rate, you'll
be in sleeping bags."

354
00:20:23,540 --> 00:20:24,540
I'll go check over there.

355
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:29,480
Found it!

356
00:20:32,180 --> 00:20:33,760
Eek! A caterpillar!

357
00:20:37,620 --> 00:20:39,110
Lucky me.

358
00:20:42,210 --> 00:20:43,210
Whoa!

359
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:52,500
(In the forest, a bird stole something important.
(Look a little lower; the bird is nearby.)

360
00:20:58,020 --> 00:20:59,220
Adachi, I'm sorry.

361
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:07,720
Dammit.

362
00:21:12,660 --> 00:21:13,820
Found it!

363
00:21:23,050 --> 00:21:24,050
Yes!

364
00:21:24,290 --> 00:21:25,490
That's one down.

365
00:21:27,930 --> 00:21:29,270
What is this, a robbery?

366
00:21:31,070 --> 00:21:32,880
Go ahead, you can have it.

367
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:38,700
Sorry about that.

368
00:21:41,180 --> 00:21:42,180
Sara...

369
00:21:42,910 --> 00:21:44,220
Stop acting so cool.

370
00:21:46,520 --> 00:21:47,660
One more to go.

371
00:21:48,850 --> 00:21:50,680
Just one more and we're done.

372
00:21:53,180 --> 00:21:55,160
You need to show him how reliable you are.

373
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:58,740
Maybe you can go from being just
acquaintances to being close juniors.

374
00:22:05,690 --> 00:22:06,690
Sara-senpai!

375
00:22:07,438 --> 00:22:09,470
Please leave the last one to me.

376
00:22:10,980 --> 00:22:11,820
Until I get back,

377
00:22:11,821 --> 00:22:13,210
just stay here and rest.

378
00:24:03,220 --> 00:24:06,670
In the forest, a bird stole
something important.

379
00:24:07,690 --> 00:24:09,700
Look a little lower.

380
00:24:10,690 --> 00:24:12,910
The bird is nearby.

381
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:16,280
It should be around here.

382
00:24:18,870 --> 00:24:20,120
This is a forest...

383
00:24:21,390 --> 00:24:24,900
The bird should be on a branch nearby.

384
00:24:44,050 --> 00:24:46,960
Where... am I?

